This paper discusses the integration of lexical semantics and pragmatics in natural language analysis, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses advances in logical formalisms associated with this framework, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions constraints on lexical transformations and polymorphic quantifiers, which could be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and compiler construction (cs.CC).
